  "title": "OPERATION MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>The Operations Manager is responsible for overseeing and optimizing the core daily functions of the business. They ensure that operations are efficient, cost-effective, and aligned with company goals by managing processes, people, and resources. - Process Management: Designs, implements, and continuously improves workflows and operational systems. - Team Leadership: Supervises, schedules, and motivates staff to achieve performance targets. - Resource Control: Manages inventory, equipment, budgets, and supplies to maximize efficiency. - Performance Monitoring:Tracks key metrics (KPIs), analyzes data, and creates reports on operational effectiveness. - Quality & Compliance:Ensures output meets quality standards and adheres to all safety and regulatory requirements. - Stakeholder Coordination: Serves as a link between departments, suppliers, and senior management. - Problem Resolution:Identifies operational issues and implements timely, effective solutions.</p>",
